<section class="how-it-works" id="how-it-works">
  <div class="container">
    <span class="section-label">Agent flow</span>
    <h2>How <span class="mono-h">agent</span> works</h2>
    <p class="section-sub">One command. No config. Claude does the thinking.</p>

    <div class="steps">
      <div class="step" data-animate data-delay="0">
        <div class="step-left">
          <div class="step-num">1</div>
          <div class="step-connector"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="step-body">
          <h4>Scan</h4>
          <p>Scans every file in your project for 50+ secret patterns and 18 OWASP code vulnerability patterns. Skips <code>node_modules</code>, test files, and binaries automatically.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="step" data-animate data-delay="80">
        <div class="step-left">
          <div class="step-num">2</div>
          <div class="step-connector"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="step-body">
          <h4>Classify with Claude</h4>
          <p>Sends findings to Claude. For each finding, Claude classifies as <span class="tag tag-red">REAL</span> (exploitable) or <span class="tag tag-gray">FALSE POSITIVE</span> (safe in context). Secrets are masked before sending — Claude never sees your actual key values.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="step" data-animate data-delay="160">
        <div class="step-left">
          <div class="step-num">3</div>
          <div class="step-connector"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="step-body">
          <h4>Remediate secrets</h4>
          <p>Confirmed real secrets are automatically rewritten to use environment variables. Source files are updated, a <code>.env</code> file is created with the actual values, and <code>.gitignore</code> is patched.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="step" data-animate data-delay="240">
        <div class="step-left">
          <div class="step-num">4</div>
          <div class="step-connector"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="step-body">
          <h4>Fix code vulnerabilities</h4>
          <p>For each real vulnerability, Claude provides a specific 1-line fix with a plain-English explanation of why the current code is exploitable and how the fix addresses it.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="step" data-animate data-delay="320">
        <div class="step-left">
          <div class="step-num">5</div>
        </div>
        <div class="step-body">
          <h4>Verify</h4>
          <p>Re-scans after remediation to confirm all secrets are gone. Shows a final clean bill of health — or a clear list of what still needs manual attention.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .mono-h {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    color: var(--cyan);
    font-size: 0.88em;
  }

  .steps {
    max-width: 640px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .step {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    padding-bottom: 0;
  }

  .step-left {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .step-num {
    width: 2.2rem;
    height: 2.2rem;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--cyan);
    color: #09090b;
    font-weight: 800;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    margin-top: 0.1rem;
    box-shadow: 0 0 16px rgba(34,211,238,0.3);
  }

  .step-connector {
    width: 2px;
    flex: 1;
    min-height: 2rem;
    background: linear-gradient(to bottom, var(--cyan-dim), rgba(14,116,144,0.1));
    margin: 0.4rem 0;
  }

  .step-body {
    padding-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .step:last-child .step-body { padding-bottom: 0; }

  .step-body h4 {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }

  .step-body p {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .step-body code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    background: var(--cyan-glow);
    color: var(--cyan);
    padding: 0.1em 0.3em;
    border-radius: 3px;
    font-size: 0.85em;
  }

  .tag {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.1em 0.5em;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-size: 0.78em;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .tag-red  { background: rgba(248,113,113,0.15); color: var(--red); border: 1px solid rgba(248,113,113,0.25); }
  .tag-gray { background: var(--bg-card); color: var(--text-muted); border: 1px solid var(--border); }
</style>
